# Import data sets
existingProductAttributes <- read.csv("existingproductattributes2017.csv")
newProductAttributes <- read.csv("newproductattributes2017.csv")

# Dummify the data
existingDummies <- dummyVars(" ~ .", data=existingProductAttributes)
newDummies <- dummyVars(" ~ .", data=newProductAttributes)

existingProducts <- data.frame(predict(existingDummies, newdata=existingProductAttributes))
newProducts <- data.frame(predict(newDummies, newdata=newProductAttributes))

# Remove attribute with NA values
existingProducts$BestSellersRank <- NULL

# Remove same column from newProducts
newProducts$BestSellersRank <- NULL

# Remove unique identifier column (ProductNum) from both data sets
existingProducts$ProductNum <- NULL
newProducts$ProductNum <- NULL

# Drop ProfitMargin column. Likely would not even be known by consumer so should have no
# effect on Volume.
existingProducts$ProfitMargin <- NULL
newProducts$ProfitMargin <- NULL

# Build correlation matrix
corrExisting <- cor(existingProducts)
